Full Description: BNY Mellon-Alcentra Mezzanine Partners is a private equity and venture capital firm specializing in mezzanine capital, buyouts, recapitalizations, acquisition financing, growth capital, and junior capital financing. It also provides senior and subordinated debt and equity capital to middle market companies.  The firm primarily invests in healthcare services, business services, defense, and government services. It prefers to invest in companies headquartered in North America with a focus on Northeast and Mid-Atlantic regions. The firm seeks to invest between $7 million and $40 million in companies with EBITDA between $5 million and $50 million. It prefers to invest between $5 million and $40 million in form of subordinated debt and between $3 million and $10 million in form of equity co-investment.  The firm typically structures its equity investments as minority co-investments. It also invests in the form of senior term loans, second lien loans, and preferred equity. The firm also participates in larger investments structured through its affiliates.  BNY Mellon-Alcentra Mezzanine Partners is based in New York, New York. It operates as a subsidiary of Alcentra NY LLC.

FreelyCall provides PBX services for its customers, including IVR, Call Forwarding, Conferencing, Voicemail, etc. FreelyCall provides its customers with free DID/Phone Number in the US, and a choice of more than 60 DIDs around the globe with rates varying between 1USD and 12USD. FreelyCall provides custom unlimited plans for customers who do not wish to worry about their minute costs. FreelyCall requires no contract for subscriptions or phone numbers, hence it's possible to cancel at any day of the month. FreelyCall has partnership with major carriers/VoIP providers around the world which allows it to control highest quality on calls and short wait duration for establishing the calls. FreelyCall allows you to choose the routing plan which suits your need. You can choose between direct/cli/premium/standard/diaer rates, or cost based routing vs quality based routing etc. FreelyCall supports FAX over IP protocol T.38 for most of its routes, and pass-thru fax over g711 for all of its routes. FreelyCall can help you port your DID/phone umber in the US and major cities around from your existing carrier to FreelyCall network for a cheap fee. FreelyCall accounts can be configured to run on virtually any device which supports the SIP protocol, so it should be easy to integrate it in your enterprise

Important applications could include targeted medical treatment, study of how DNA changes chemically over a lifetime, targeted health and fitness regimens, and genealogical reporting and ability to pass stored DNA to future generations. The GENiSYSS DNA Vault offers room temperature DNA storage and co-located digital data on a flash drive which is encrypted and password protected.
